Description:
TECHNICAL PROJECT MANAGER
INVEST OTTAWA -
AREA X.O
Do you have a passion for innovation? Are you interested in joining a collaborative team? If yes, we strongly encourage you to apply to our posting and join the Area X.O Team!
WHY THIS ROLE
:
Reporting to the CEO, the Technical Project Manager will work as part of a team to drive the execution for the Area X.O program which provides advanced technology testing, training, and prototyping in support of clean, connected communities. This includes programming such as the
Autonomous Vehicle Innovation Network (AVIN
) Regional Technology Hub www.avinhub.ca. The Project Manager role has shared responsibilities for technical operations, project management, and maintaining the quality of services provided for the hub.
The Project Manager, in collaboration with the Area X.O team and the industry technical steering committee, will design and establish the private and public multi-vendor test platforms. These platforms will integrate various AVIN partners in-kind contributions into cohesive testbeds.
The ideal candidate will play a key role in the technical operation of the Centre and be an expert network architect with a strong engineering track record in data centric cloud services, communications, and IT networks.
WHAT YOU WILL BE DOING
:
Defining processes, project requirements and policies through customer interaction, market research, quantitative sizing, competitive analysis, and by working with the AVIN partners;
Working with the industry partners, establish a public and private, integrated, multi-vendor AV test platform that supports Area X.O / AVIN projects, use cases and research from the stakeholders across the regions AV cluster;
Working with the technical steering committee and with the industry partners define, deliver and continue to evolve the public and private AVIN testbeds;
Identifying and evaluating AVIN projects with partners and reporting for industry projects;
Playing a key role in ensuring that all projects and metrics are met and delivered to the government funders in the required timelines;
Estimating budget and scope for testing and developmental projects;
Providing trouble-shooting and technical support to clients related to device integration, and relevant testing and development activities;
Researching and evaluate hardware and software technology options when making large purchases on behalf of the company;
Providing training related to Area X.O capabilities and services to clients and partners;
Developing, update, and monitor Area X.O asset register and service catalogue;
Working with cross-functional groups to translate customer project requirements into technical specifications and system-level blueprint for the testbed environment;
Facilitating solution development and deployment of complex IoT / V2X solutions including network connectivity, product & project testing, proofs-of-concepts, and customer trials;
Contributing to the design, implementation, and management of the V2X testbed, advanced IoT domains, remote monitoring systems, and hybrid multi-cloud data network – Microsoft Azure, AWS, API engines for vendor-specific clouds etc.
WHAT YOU HAVE ACCOMPLISHED
/ GAINED THROUGHOUT YOUR CAREER:
Bachelor’s degree or College Diploma in Engineering or Computer Science;
5-7 years hands-on experience in project management, preferably with software or networking systems;
Background in network architecture and integration methodologies related to new technologies such as 5G NR (NSA/SA), LTE, LP-WAN, NB-IoT, LoRa, and SDN;
Strong knowledge of IP networking stack, transport communication protocols, web applications environments, including virtual private networks (VPN), TCP/IP, SSL/TLS, MQTT, HTTPS, DNS, routing, load balancing, etc.;
Experience with virtualized computing and network monitoring environments like VMware VCentre, VSphere, Openstack, OpenNMS, Solarwinds etc.;
Industry experiences in automotive, transportation, agriculture, defence and security including first-responders markets would be considered an asset;
Ability to design and present technical artifacts at varying degrees of technical depth to a wide range of audience;
Working knowledge of data analytics, data visualization, cloud-based solutions, IoT, and advanced network services;
Excellent time management, problem-solving, and organizational skills;
Sound judgment and ability in handling matters of a confidential and/or sensitive nature;
Ability to communicate effectively and collaborate in a team environment;
Certified Project Management Professional is an asset;
Do you have some of these skills but maybe not all? We still encourage you to apply as we would love to review your unique application and learn more about you!
